2017 WW52 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver Release Announcement (BKC #37)

DEG Platform Integration Team

\n \n
\n\n \n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW52 Bakerville/SKX-D Silver release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\n \n ESXi6.5/\n \n RHEL7.3/\n \n WS2016\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Li, Feng Y.\n

Bakerville(RP Board: Yuba\nCity RP fab3)

  • Total\ntest cases: 28; Passed test cases is 28 and pass rate is 100%
  • Test coverage: SKX-D M1 SoC(QP3M & QNNN): Run P1 and P2 test cases.

Notes: The HSD 5346596 is hit on ROW QS Parts: QDF QNNT.

5346596  [2017_WW48][BIOS:04D93][Bakerville_SKXD]\nsystem easily hang at code EE when doing warm reboot with QNNT CPU


Known Issue/Errata:

5345768 [2016_WW52][BIOS:D05][Purley_SKX]SUT hang when running warm boot cycling.

Status: Will not be fixed in Purley family. Details can be found 5345768 in HSD

HW rework:

    \n
  • No HW rework need for Yuba City\n fab3 board.
    • \n
  • jumper setting refers to\n this link.
    • \n

 Work\naround:

    \n
  • Secure Boot only can run in\n UEFI mode, so if we want secure boot can work and let bios load UEFI\n Oprom, we need Disable this option. 
    • \n

EDKII\nMenu -> Boot Options -> EFI INT10 workaround

    \n
  • When you flash onboard Aspeed\n BMC, in order to detect onboard dTPM in AC cycle, you need run below IPMI\n command in UEFI Shell:
    • \n
